      "root_cause": "LLM sees 'search my notes', 'open my note', 'my daily note' and routes to memory_recall because _INTENT_SYSTEM description for memory_recall says 'what YOU remember about their setup'. Notes queries are semantically similar to memory queries.",
      "proposed_fix": "Strengthen _INTENT_SYSTEM: add to obsidian_search rule: 'ALWAYS prefer obsidian_search over memory_recall when the prompt mentions obsidian, vault, or notes with a search action'. Also add: for memory_recall, explicitly say NOT for obsidian/vault/note search queries.",
      "affected_file": "adwi/adwi_cli.py \u2014 _INTENT_SYSTEM",
